# {{brand.name}} â€” Design System Rules

> These rules are **enforced by hooks** under `.claude/hooks/`. A pre-save hook will warn (or block) on violations.

## Token rules (no hardcoding)

- **Colors:** Use only `var(--color-*)` (semantic) or `var(--primary-*|deep-*|gray-*)` (primitive). **Never** raw hex like `#000000` in component code.
- **Spacing:** Use Tailwind utilities (`p-4`, `gap-3`, `mt-8`). **Never** raw pixel values like `padding: 17px`.
- **Typography:** Use the fluid utility classes (`.text-display-xl`, `.text-display`, `.text-h1`, `.text-h2`, `.text-h3`) for headings, Tailwind defaults (`text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`) for body. **Never** raw `text-[28px]` ladders.
- **Radius:** Tailwind utilities (`rounded-full`, `rounded-2xl`). No `border-radius: 17px`.
- **Shadows:** Tailwind utilities (`shadow-md`, `shadow-xl`) or `var(--shadow-*)`.

## Allowed exceptions

These are legitimately raw values (the hook ignores them):

- **`app/globals.css`** â€” primitive `:root` block. Hex defined here, referenced everywhere else.
- **Motion durations:** `0.28s`, `0.7s`, `[0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]` ease arrays â€” timing constants, not style tokens.
- **Z-index integers:** `z-30`, `z-50` â€” Tailwind utility; raw integers are also allowed in inline `style={{ zIndex: 60 }}`.
- **Aspect ratios:** `"16 / 10"`, `"4 / 3"` â€” geometry, not style.
- **`scripts/**`** â€” utility scripts, not product code.
- **`docs/**`** â€” documentation examples in fenced code blocks.

